channel.title: Equality :: Introduction to Web Dev
channel.description: Loose Equality With == In the section booleans , we learned about the comparison operators == and !=, which test whether two values are equal or not equal, respectively. However, there are some quirks with using the == operator, which occur when we use == to compare different data types. Example console.log(7 == "7"); console.log(0 == false); console.log(0 == '');
